<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - REAR COVER, FLYWHEEL, and POWER STEERING GEAR DRIVE - Rear Cover
        and Power Steering Idler Shaft
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Rear Cover and Power Steering Idler Shaft</title>
        <figure id="f2651320" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD06/D06150.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 472. Rear cover mounting bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolts marked A, (M10 x 55) (5)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolts marked B, (M10 x 70) (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolts marked C, (M10 x 60) (4)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bolts from rear cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or possible death, use a suitable lifting device or get help when
                    removing the rear cover.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2651321" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd06/D0607.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 473. Rear cover assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove rear cover assembly with the aid of an assistant.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the hydraulic pump cover is in place, make sure the hydraulic pump cover gasket does not
                        pull out when removing the rear cover. Also avoid pulling out the gasket between the upper and
                        lower crankcase.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If required, the power steering idler shaft can be removed using a slide hammer.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
